    "Figure 3:3Figure 3: Schematic of ViT-based encoder used in vipr.",
    "The example illustrates the configuration for 5 output classes (corresponding to 4 mass bins plus a non-halo class).",
    "The input 3D volume is divided into patches, which are flattened, projected into a K-dimensional embedding space, and enriched with positional encodings.",
    "These embeddings are then processed through a series of transformer blocks.",
    "The resulting output is passed to a CNN-based decoder, which reconstructs voxel-wise classification probabilities."
